Bitdefender is a cybersecurity leader delivering best-in-class threat prevention, detection, and response solutions worldwide. Guardian over millions of consumer, business, and government environments, Bitdefender is the industryâ€™s trusted expert for eliminating threats, protecting privacy and data, and enabling cyber resiliency. With deep investments in research and development, Bitdefender Labs discovers 400 new threats each minute and validates 30 billion threat queries daily. The company has pioneered breakthrough innovations in antimalware, IoT security, behavioral analytics, and artificial intelligence and its technology is licensed by more than 150 of the worldâ€™s most recognized technology brands. Founded in 2001, Bitdefender has customers in 170 countries with offices around the world. 
The Director of Business Applications and Project Management will lead the Business Solutions Group (BSG) Application and Project management team to align critical systems and processes with BSG strategy and mentor and develop a high performing team of Application and Project managers. This role will transform and manage the Technology Stack and related processes and projects for BSG   including CRM, PRM, CPQ, order management, marketing automation and related applications. The successful candidate will understand and translate the businessâ€™ technology needs to the applications and IT teams, will have strong cross-functional communication and management skills, and a solution-oriented mindset. 
Responsibilities 
Strategize with business and IT leaders to develop and execute Technology Stack roadmap for BSG 
Transform current Tech Stack to achieve high-growth objectives and better serve partners and sales teams 
Lead and develop BSG Applications and Project management team 
Analyze and maximize current Tech Stack and processes and recommend improvements to current approach 
Collaborate and drive initiatives with Applications, Security and IT teams 
Manage and prioritize projects and BAU with stakeholders 
Manage significant implementation projects for business unit 
Skills & Experience 
10+ years CRM and related business application management in high tech environment 
Track record of successful collaboration and delivery of large-scale projects 
Understanding of lead to cash process from both a business and systems perspective 
Salesforce experience required, esp. integrations, application management, process automation 
Ability to absorb details of each function to map out end-to-end processes and systems 
Strong problem-solving abilities 
Ability to manage and develop global team 
Manage multiple projects concurrently 
Extensive project management skills and capacity and willingness to transfer to teams 
Ability to effectively communicate business needs to technology teams 
